moduleDescription: This module aims to provide a thorough understanding of health assessment and to develop advanced skills in performing history taking and physical examination. These skills are essential for diagnostic reasoning and clinical decision-making. Principles and techniques from the physical, health, and behavioural sciences are utilised to obtain health assessment data and make differential diagnoses and subsequently, the final diagnosis.
faculty: YONG LOO LIN SCHOOL OF MEDICINE
